com/gigapixel-ai) **v7.2.3**\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the latest version with [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/gigapixel/)\n\n```bash\npip install -U gigapixel\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom gigapixel import Gigapixel\n\ngp = Gigapixel(r\"C:\\Program Files\\Topaz Labs LLC\\Topaz Gigapixel AI\\Topaz Gigapixel AI.exe\")\n\ngp.process(r\"path\\to\\image.jpg\")\n```\n\nAdditional parameters can be passed to `process()` method:\n```python\nfrom gigapixel import Scale, Mode\n\ngp.process(\n  r\"path\\to\\image.jpg\",\n  scale=Scale.X2,\n  mode=Mode.STANDARD,\n)\n```\n\n> **Warning!**\n> Using parameters (`scale`, `mode`) may take **additional time** to process single image.\n> Consider using them only when needed.\n> To get the best performance, use `gp.process(r\"path\\to\\image.jpg\")`\n\n\n## Contributing\n\nBug reports and/or pull requests are welcome\n\n\n## License\n\nThe module is available as open source under the terms of the [Apache License, Version 2.0](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "gigapixel.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "gigapixel.exceptions.GigapixelException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "gigapixel.exceptions.NotFile", "bases": ["GigapixelException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "gigapixel.exceptions.FileAlreadyExists", "bases": ["GigapixelException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "gigapixel.exceptions.ElementNotFound", "bases": ["GigapixelException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "gigapixel", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exp